A "legal request to have a case reviewed by a higher authority." It's almost quaint, isn't it? As if a different set of eyes, further up the bureaucratic food chain, will suddenly conjure perfect clarity from the messy chaos of human error. One might almost call it hope, if one were prone to such sentimental nonsense.

"Appellant" redirects here. For rhetorical appeals, see [Modes of persuasion](/Modes_of_persuasion). For appealing blocks on wikipedia, see [Wikipedia:Appealing a block](/Wikipedia:Appealing_a_block). For other uses, see [Appeal (disambiguation)](/Appeal_(disambiguation)) and [Appellants](/Appellants_(disambiguation)).

